metadata.name: SquarePlus #112
metadata.description:
A study of basic shapes ended up with Squares or Pluses. Each layer has a different color code along with a point-related rotation and scale which result in an elegant composition.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje Februari 2023

metadata.name: Curtains #46
metadata.description:
Curtains

While learning more about flow fields, as an intermediate step, the first version of this came out.
The artwork creates a set of lines; the first point of the lines are anchors, which can be in a straight line, sinus wave, or tangent function.
The second point is set by calculating the angle from the first using Perlin noise.

The project features 10 different hand-picked color schemes.

Actions:
--------------
Press [s] to save
--------------


Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Multidimensional Maximalism #9
metadata.description:
Multidimensional Maximalism is my learning experience with layering and composition.

Using the Cellular Automaton algorithm from "Gen., Machina" we create multiple dimensions of life. Each with it's own unique evolution and structure. Like petri dishes in a lab. We then use different compositional elements to explore these dimensions.

100% code - as always.

Available overlays
--
* Lasers (drawing inspiration from The Harvest by Per Kristian Stoveland)
* Circleblend
* Drops
* Lenses
* Squares
* Crazysquares
* Waves
* Tesseract (drawing inspiration from the awesome Tesseract collection by Studio Yorktown)
* None (unlucky you)

Controls (in live view):
--
Press [1-9] to set the export scale ratio
Press [s] to save a high resolution image [ resolution x scale ]

enjoy.

metadata.name: Broken Angles #21
metadata.description:
Angles represent the artist's view of the space and the visible subject, and the position is chosen so that the audience is able to see the subject from that angle.
The angles determine the audience's point of view in this way and by changing the angles, the audience can see the subject of the image from a new perspective.
Made by p5.js
s = save

metadata.name: Skies and Lands #58
metadata.description:
Skies and Lands is a collection of generative art featuring a house as the protagonist in an endless array of distinct landscapes. Each piece in the collection showcases a unique representation of the house located in different lands, with varied and dramatic skies providing a captivating contrast. The combination of the static architecture with the constantly changing landscape creates a stunning and never-before-seen visual experience. "Skies and Lands" collection invites the viewer to explore new perspectives and to enjoy the beauty of architecture and nature together. A timeless work of art that will undoubtedly delight art and nature lovers alike.

Don't miss the chance to own a piece of this unique and captivating collection.

metadata.name: Neuromorphosis #88
metadata.description:
The relationship between biology and technology in the future.

Inspired by Neurons and their role in transmitting information, creating dynamic shapes and patterns that evoke brain activity. Where technology and biology combine to create a new form of intelligence and consciousness.

It's a call to reflect on the impact of technology on our society and relationship with humans and the natural world.


🧬 Press "d" to download in png.

🧬 Made with p5.js
